Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with trefoil symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 46. Name, Istros. Same die as Alexandria Museum, ALEX ABC 0369.42.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0755)
